# Pause Asset Builder Rules

This repo is in a client-handoff state. Before changing templates, builder UI, colors, logos, uploads, or styleguide content, read `AI_GENERATION_RULES.md`.

Core rules:

- Preserve the current branded direction: warm analog podcast assets, dark plum/near-black app chrome, ivory text, lavender metadata, amber accents.
- Use only the existing design-system palette for user-facing color controls. Do not add freeform color pickers.
- Keep preview/export templates visually isolated from the surrounding builder UI. Dark mode applies outside the preview container unless the user asks to alter exported artwork.
- Use existing brand assets and components: `TwoColorLogo`, `LogoAvatar`, `KickerPill`, `Texture`, `Deco`, `PaletteDropdown`, and `BrushClockLoader`.
- Do not reintroduce corner flourishes.
- For horizontal Episode Cover and Guest Announcement photo layouts, keep the rounded-square `LogoAvatar` as the logo treatment and avoid duplicate standalone logos.
- Image uploads are optional; empty image areas should remain clean branded space without placeholder labels in exported templates.
- Preserve image compression for uploads and PNG transparency for Main Cover cutouts.
- After substantive edits, run `npm run build` and check lints for changed files.
